attributes.PROJECT_FULL_TITLE: Internal hydrogen infrastructure in Denmark [currently known as DK Hydrogen Pipeline West]
attributes.TECHNICAL_DESCR:
National infrastructure project connecting the hydrogen storage project Lille Torup in Northern Denmark as well as electrolysis plants in the region of Esbjerg in Western Denmark with Germany. The project aims to develop a 347 km 100% hydrogen infrastructure composed of new (254 km) and converted (93 km) onshore pipelines.

The project currently consists of:

  • New 19 km from the hydrogen storage project Lille Torup to Tjele, 
  • New 71 km from Tjele to Idomlund, 
  • New 55 km from Idomlund to Stovstrup, 
  • New 42 km from Stovstrup to Endrup, 
  • New 38 km from Endrup to Egtved, 
  • New 25 km from Egtved to Landerupgård, 
  • New 4 km from Landerupgård to Ryttergård, 
  • Converted 93 km from Egtved to Frøslev (DK)/Ellund (DE).

The hydrogen transmission capacity at the PCI Denmark-Germany interconnection point is 556 Mt/y (60 GWh/d).
attributes.IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS_DESCR: Planned but not yet in permitting
